heading_context: June survey of agriculture and horticulture
chunks.html_content:
You must complete Defra’s June agricultural survey if you’re selected and you live in England. You’ll get an email request or a survey form in the post in late May or early June.

You’ll need to supply information about the land, crops, livestock and workers on your farm.

Contact the Defra Surveys Team if you’re having problems accessing the survey or if you have any queries about agricultural surveys.

You’ll have to complete a different survey if you live outside of England.

You’ll be contacted by the Scottish Government, Welsh Government or the Department for Agricultural and Rural Development in Northern Ireland if you need to complete a survey.
